  "texts": [
    "The η = 0 curve reproduces the familiar hyperbola of the standard Heisenberg Uncertainty Principle (HUP), where ∆p diverges as ∆x → 0 and vanishes as ∆x → ∞.",
    "In contrast, for negative η, the uncertainty behavior changes qualitatively: ∆p no longer approaches zero at large ∆x, but instead saturates at a finite minimal value, ∆p min, which increases with |η|.",
    "This saturation reflects the infrared (IR) modifications to momentum space introduced by the Extended Uncertainty Principle (EUP).",
    "For visual clarity, we use illustrative values of η on the order of 10 -1 in Figure 1 many orders of magnitude larger than the phenomenologically consistent value (η ∼ 10 -27).",
    "This rescaling preserves the qualitative features of the curves while enhancing their visual distinction."
  ],
